    "Problem Formalization": "The hydraulic head \\(h(\\mathbf{x})\\) is the primary unknown on a known domain \\(\\Omega\\). The steady‑state Darcy flow is described by the elliptic PDE:\n\\[ -\\nabla\\cdot\\big(K(\\mathbf{x})\\,\\nabla h(\\mathbf{x})\\big) = Q(\\mathbf{x}), \\quad \\mathbf{x}\\in\\Omega, \\]\nwhere \\(K(\\mathbf{x})\\) is the spatially varying, fully known permeability (or hydraulic conductivity) field, and \\(Q(\\mathbf{x})\\) denotes source/sink terms. If a source term is not supplied it must be treated as unknown and will appear as an additional modelling gap. Boundary conditions are assumed available: a Dirichlet condition \\(h = h_D\\) on \\(\\Gamma_D\\) and/or a Neumann flux condition \\( -K\\nabla h \\cdot \\mathbf{n} = q_N\\) on \\(\\Gamma_N\\).

